<body>
    <h1>Developer Guide</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <p>eZ Publish 5.x is a &quot;Dual kernel&quot; software. This means=
 it contains both a <em>legacy</em> <em>kernel</em> (effectively a &quot;4.=
y&quot; version) aka &quot;Legacy Stack&quot;, and a new <em>5.x kernel</em=
>, aka &quot;Symfony Stack&quot; (because it uses <a href=3D"http://symfony=
.com/about" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Symfony2</a> Fullstack=
&nbsp;framework).</p>
<h2 id=3D"DeveloperGuide-Legacykernel">Legacy kernel</h2>
<p>For documentation on the <em>legacy kernel</em>, please go to <a href=3D=
"http://doc.ez.no" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">doc.ez.no</a> w=
here you'll find documentation on everything from it's GUIs, official exten=
sions to template coding&nbsp;( 5.x doc:&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://doc.ez.no/e=
Z-Publish/User-manual/5.x" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">User ma=
nual</a> &amp;&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://doc.ez.no/eZ-Publish/Technical-manual=
/5.x" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Technical manual</a> ). If y=
ou are looking for documentation on how to develop extensions for legacy in=
 php, then also see relevant material on <a href=3D"http://share.ez.no" cla=
ss=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">share.ez.no</a> ( <a href=3D"http://s=
hare.ez.no/learn/ez-publish" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">Tutor=
ials</a>,&nbsp;<a href=3D"http://share.ez.no/blogs" class=3D"external-link"=
 rel=3D"nofollow">Blogs</a>&nbsp;).</p>
<h2 id=3D"DeveloperGuide-5.xkernel">5.x kernel</h2>
<p>The new 5.x kernel is built using an HMVC model. It currently consists o=
f Public API (Model), Symfony2 Fullstack&nbsp;Framework&nbsp;(Hierarchical =
View Controller) with Twig (template engine) enhanced with eZ Publish&nbsp;=
concepts (Core Bundle).&nbsp;On top of these you'll find REST v2 API, Demo =
Bundle and a Legacy Bundle allowing some integration between the two kernel=
s.</p>
<p>For&nbsp;documentation&nbsp;on Symfony2 go to <a href=3D"http://symfony.=
com/doc/current/index.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">symfon=
y.com</a>&nbsp;(for&nbsp;Twig see <a href=3D"http://symfony.com/doc/current=
/book/templating.html" class=3D"external-link" rel=3D"nofollow">here</a>)&n=
bsp;and for the eZ Publish parts of 5.x kernel continue reading in this sec=
tion of our new wiki&nbsp;documentation area.</p>
    </div>
</body>
